text: Devastated and frustrated that 5 people were shot at @MorganStateU last night. I thank our first responders and pray for the victims. A night of celebration turned into terror and it’s all too common in the US today. Common sense, life-saving gun safety reforms are long overdue.

Breast cancer is the most common cancer in the world.

As Breast Cancer Awareness Month begins, I want to remind you about the importance of getting your annual screenings. It could save your life.

Repping my O’s tie! Congrats to the @Orioles on clinching the AL East championship, winning 100 games this season and signing a 30-year contract extension on Camden Yards. No one deserves it more. Go O’s! #Birdland

Maryland families can't afford an extreme MAGA shutdown.

House Republicans must put the needs of the majority over the loud few and pass a government funding bill now.

Read my @baltimoresun op-ed with @RepDavidTrone here: baltimoresun.com/opinion/op-…

I'm deeply saddened to hear my friend, Sen. Dianne Feinstein, has passed. We both served as the top Dems on the Intel Committees, where she was the first female chair and worked to protect our national security. She leaves a strong legacy of service. My prayers are w/ her family.
Thank you all for you kind words.

With a heavy heart, I announce the passing of my wonderful mother, Peggy, at age 101. My mother was relentlessly positive -- we called her Pollyanna Peggy - and a huge inspiration to me throughout my public service. @BaltimoreSun obit: baltimoresun.com/obituaries/…

It’s always great to catch up with fellow Baltimoreans in the halls of democracy! Sat down with my good friend and Baltimore County Councilman, @julianejonesjr, and discussed how a government shutdown will impact #MD02. We must reach a compromise!
I am saddened to hear of the passing of @Orioles Hall of Famer, Brooks Robinson. Brooks was the all time best third baseman and one heck of a nice guy. I am sending his family my prayers.
It’s time to get serious and advance reasonable spending bills that don’t kick teachers out of classrooms and bring us closer to a government shutdown.

Republicans are trying to advance an education de-funding bill this week that would remove nearly 4,400 teachers from #Maryland classrooms (amid an already-severe national teacher shortage) as a result of Title 1 cuts.

To all who are observing, I wish you a blessed Yom Kippur and a meaningful fast.
 
G'mar Chatima Tovah!

Congratulations, @GenCQBrownJr, on your confirmation as chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, our nation’s top military officer, as well as soon-to-be-confirmed Generals Randy George & Eric Smith.

I look forward to your continued success and steady leadership.

Sat down with the incredible @BillNye and @exploreplanets leadership yesterday and discussed the importance of investing in space science & exploration. Space has long been a passion and priority of mine, so it was a treat to meet one of its most famous advocates!

This Nat'l #RecoveryMonth, I'm standing by my colleagues on both sides of the aisle to raise awareness & honor those in recovery. In 2022, nearly 110,000 American lives were lost to overdose. I'm committed to driving that number down. Recovery is for everyone. #CongressGoesPurple

#TeamMaryland announced over $900k in @HHSGov funding to provide free COVID-19 vaccinations to Marylanders. As COVID-19 cases rise across the country, it is important that Marylanders can be protected from the virus and keep those around them safe. More: ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Older LGBTQI+ Americans are disproportionately impacted by HIV. Thankfully, we have tools to prevent & manage the disease. I’m committed to improving access to treatment to ensure long & happy lives for all people aging with HIV.

Know your status. Get tested. Take action. #NHAAD

#TeamDutch's Danielle visited the Balt Co African American Cultural Festival this weekend, founded in 1996 by @SpeakerAJones & me. The event was well-attended by locals who enjoyed food, music & regional vendors. Kudos to the organizers who bring the festival to life each year!

Everyday is a great day to be a Baltimorean but this weekend was exceptional. The @Ravens won, the @Orioles advanced to the postseason and @SimplyAJ10 retires as an Oriole. Go O’s in the playoffs! #Birdland #ravensnation

Shanah Tovah to all those observing Rosh Hashanah in #MD02, throughout the United States and across the world. 
 
May the Jewish New Year bring peace and joy to all.
This Hispanic Heritage Month, I celebrate and recognize all of the ways that Latino Americans in #MD02 and throughout the country have shaped this great nation and continue to make it better.

America has been rebounding and a government shutdown will take us two steps back. I implore House leadership to remove the irrelevant, hyper-partisan provisions in these funding bills and reach a compromise for the good of the country. More: ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Enjoyed a visit from @TFABaltimore and learning more about what they are doing to help students and teachers at home in #MD02. Thank you for helping to ensure every child has the opportunity to succeed!

Today, I met with a group of @MaryKay Independent Beauty Consultants, including some #MD02 constituents. We discussed entrepreneurship, women’s empowerment and how the federal government can support businesswomen!
8000 troops from 34 countries participated in this year's training exercise in Egypt to enhance regional and global security.

Without the expanded #ChildTaxCredit, the child poverty rate rose from 5.2% to 12.4% between 2021 and 2022. Child poverty is a policy choice.

This is a wake up call – Congress must restore this lifeline for America's working families.

On the 22nd anniversary of the 9/11 attacks, let us honor the victims, their families, survivors and first responders who saved so many lives that day. May we continue to work towards a world of peace and understanding. #NeverForget
Congratulations to Baltimore native, @BishmeCromartie, on winning #PRAllStars. You are further proof that Baltimore is home to some of the greatest. Wishing you continued success!

Today, #TeamMaryland announced $8.7 million in funding from the #bipartisan infrastructure law to modernize Maryland’s power grid and invest in clean energy. Updating our power grid will save taxpayer dollars and better prepare the state for emergencies. ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Happy Labor Day! Today we celebrate American workers & the proud history of the labor movement.

America's workforce is the backbone of our economy & our prosperity. Let's pass the #PROAct and the #RaisetheWageAct to give workers the level playing field they deserve. #LaborDay

September is Suicide Prevention Awareness Month. To those who are struggling – please know that you are not alone and that help is available. 
 
If you or a loved one is in crisis, call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline for free, confidential help 24/7.

Thanks in part to my legislation, all 50 states now have approved plans to reimburse victims of #SNAP theft. This abhorrent crime remains pervasive and I look forward to securing a permanent fix by including HR 205 in the next #farmbill.

Last week, I attended the @MDCounties #MACOCon in @OCMaryland. So great to connect with govt colleagues at the federal, state & local level & learn how we can work better together on behalf of our constituents! Pictured here with “Flat Dutch” at my shared booth with @RepSarbanes.

Earlier this month, #TeamDutch’s Danielle joined constituents at the 124th Annual Elks Grand Lodge and 120th Grand Temple Daughters of Elks International Convention. Over 1,000 attendees filled 5 hotels in Baltimore for the convention – an incredible turnout!

This evening, I met with CEO of @STEERTechLLC, Anuja Sonalker, at @MDCounties #MACoCon. We discussed automated vehicle technology developed by the #Maryland start-up. Always learning more about how government can help female-owned businesses succeed!

One year ago today, the #InflationReductionAct became law. The IRA reduces costs for Americans, invests in America, makes the tax code more equitable & is the most ambitious climate action in history. Learn how the IRA is making a difference for Americans: whitehouse.gov/briefing-room…

Moms working full-time, year-round earn just 62 cents, compared to dads' full dollar. Today's #MomsEqualPayDay should remind us all that Moms should not have to choose between caring for themselves and loved ones and earning a paycheck!

Making a difference in the lives of working Marylanders is very important to me. Especially our working mothers! This #MomsEqualPayDay, I am advocating for #paycheckfairness to ensure moms get their fair share!

There are 129,831 #SocialSecurity recipients in #MD02. 88 years after FDR signed the original Social Security Act into law, it’s time to expand and enhance benefits for the most vulnerable members of our communities.

On this Social Security National Day of Action, I want to voice my support for Social Security 2100. If Congress does not act, workers who retire after 2034 will receive only 77% of their full #SocialSecurity benefits. #Marylanders deserve 100%!

#TeamDutch's David visited #Maryland start-up @STEERTechLLC today to check out their autonomous vehicle fleet.  STEER Tech is among the first to put a self-parking feature in the hands of consumers. So great to see a local, woman-owned biz doing big things in the tech world!

Thanks to @DHSgov preparedness grants, #TeamMaryland was able to secure over $15 million to strengthen security at houses of worship. With this funding, they will be equipped with the latest tools to keep their communities across Maryland #safe. ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

#TeamMaryland announced nearly $70 million in FY23 @DHSgov preparedness grants to ensure that first responders are better equipped at handling emergency situations — enabling them to save more lives. #Marylanders deserve to feel safe in their communities. ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Had a great time with my fellow #Terps at the @UofMaryland Terps on the Hill reception last night, including running into a former #MD02 intern who now works for @tedlieu! Terps are changing the world. Pictured also w/ @RepStenyHoyer @President_Pines @kevinwillard #feartheturtle

I am proud be to a cosponsor of the #bipartisan legislation introduced by @RepSarbanes and @ChrisVanHollen to create a unified Chesapeake National Recreation Area. Saving the Chesapeake Bay means saving jobs for Marylanders. Read more: ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Yesterday, the House Army Caucus hosted a reception showcasing @USArmy’s modernization efforts essential to our national security. It’s an honor to co-chair this #bipartisan caucus! Pictured here w/ Hon. Doug Bush @ArmyASAALT, @rep_stevewomack & Gen James E. Rainey of @armyfuture

Great pick by @POTUS in @MartinOMalley to lead @SocialSecurity -- an agency critical to so many of my constituents. He's the right person at the right time -- smart, efficient, data-driven. I hope my Senate colleagues quickly confirm him.

#TeamMaryland also announced over $28 million in @HHSGov funding for @HeadStartgov programs across #Maryland to expand early learning, development, health and family well-being. By supporting Head Start programs, we are setting our children up for success. ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

#TeamMaryland announced $497,861 in Inflation Reduction Act funding to identify & combat air pollutants in underserved MD communities. With this funding, @MDEnvironment can improve the health of those living in low-income and minority neighborhoods. ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Our chief-of-staff, Tara, met with @GilmanSchool's Jameson Maumenee last week and was so impressed with his questions on politics and journalism! Jameson, a rising senior, was a national youth correspondent at the Washington Journalism and Media Conference held @GeorgeMasonU.

#TeamDutch's Danielle attended the grand opening of the @MercyMedCenter Personal Physicians in #MD02's Hunt Valley last week. Excited my constituents will have greater access to leading-edge primary healthcare where they live, shop and work!
My grandson, Charlie, made a new friend at today’s @WhiteHouse picnic! Thanks @POTUS!
Ran into my friend, @guyton42b, in the halls of democracy today! Michelle does a great job advocating for our mutual #MD02 constituents!

Republican's cuts are not numbers on a page. This is the air in our skies and in our lungs. This is water we drink, bathe and cook with. It's the #ChesapeakeBay. Watch @AppropsDems fight to protect these necessities from these dangerous cuts at 10 AM. piped.video/EsyFG6yY-qk

While @AppropsDems are working to rebuild America’s infrastructure, the '24 transportation funding bill put forth by House Republicans reverses the progress we have made. Their cuts make us less safe. Watch us debate the bill @ 10:30 AM: piped.video/m-os0XtmfdA
Tagging you, @AssalilLei72960!
Thank you, @CodyLDorsey, for making our community a better place!

Our #TeamDutch comms director was interviewed by Leila Assalil of Winter Mills HS in #Westminster #MD02 @CCPsk12 as part of the @WJMC_Mason #WJMC conference yesterday. So encouraging to see whip-smart students from the district interested in journalism, a staple of democracy!
More good news on the #economy following reports earlier this week that inflation is falling sharply!
Congratulations, @MayorBMScott! Children are life's greatest gifts.

Which is the party of law and order? House Republicans' bill to fund our primary federal law enforcement efforts for FY2024 is $25 billion – 29% – below 2023. I'm standing up for public safety and just voted NO with @AppropsDems.

The #FSGG funding bill we considered in committee today:
🧸makes unsafe products available to children
💵leaves seniors vulnerable to scammers
☎️increases robocalls
I joined @AppropsDems in voting NO. Let's take our job seriously and responsibly fund the government.

House Republicans are reversing our nation's position on the world stage. From military to economic to humanitarian aid, their 2024 funding bill unravels the hard-fought credibility & influence we have earned as global leaders. Watch us mark-up the bill: piped.video/knBgSTg3NU8

I urge the Senate to expediently confirm Gen. C.Q. Brown, Jr., as our next chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff. It is unconscionable to delay confirmations critical to our natl security -- including Rear Adm. Yvette Davis as the next superintendent of the @USNA – over politics.

#TeamMaryland announced over $650,000 in federal funding for @MarylandDNR to control the spread of wildlife diseases; namely, the highly-contagious avian flu. These diseases pose a massive threat to local farmers, fisheries, our economy and food supply. ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

.@SenatorCardin, @ChrisVanHollen and I announced $1,273,989 in @ENERGY funding to improve the learning environment, air quality & health outcomes for students & staff at @WatershedPCS. The #Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill continues to benefit our community! ruppersberger.house.gov/news…
And if there was indeed an intelligence failure, I expect a full and transparent investigation with all those responsible held accountable. We have to do better.

Struggling to find the words to describe the heartache over yet another mass shooting, this time in a community I represented for decades. The people of #baltimore #Brooklyn deserve to gather and celebrate together without fear for their lives. It’s ridiculous.

College should be as accessible to all students, and without crippling debt. Businesses that are open to the public should be just that. These are simple truths that should be acknowledged by a fair and impartial #SCOTUS.

#TeamMaryland announced $3.8 million in @USDA funding to help MD-based food businesses increase their capacity to process meat and invasive Blue Catfish in the state. This means more business for our farmers and watermen and lower food costs for consumers. ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Yesterday, #TeamMaryland announced $1.5 million in #Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill funding to make safety improvements to the Warner Street Highway-Rail crossing in Baltimore City. Let’s keep Baltimore moving! ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Today, #TeamMaryland announced $25 million in #Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill funding to repair old trails, construct new paths and improve overall safety on the Capital Trails Network. These trails are important to connecting people and neighborhoods in #Maryland and DC!

Airport safety is non-negotiable. That is why @RepLaLota and I introduced #bipartisan legislation to create a dedicated funding source for airport security screening, drawing from the Passenger Security Fee that all customers already pay when buying an airline ticket. Read more:

#TeamMaryland announced over $267 million in #Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill funding to expand access to affordable, reliable, high-speed broadband. A huge step in strengthening our broadband infrastructure & ensuring that no Marylander is left behind! ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

In February, #TeamMaryland wrote to @SecretaryPete in support of MDOT funding. Today, we announced $20 million in federal funding for @mtamaryland’s Mondawmin RAISE Transit Hub Project to improve transit infrastructure and accessibility at the station. ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

No community is immune from the disgusting antisemetic and anti-LGBTQ+ trends we’re seeing nationwide, including our own. Our diversity is our strength and I hope those responsible are investigated. I will always stand up and speak out against hate.

#TeamMaryland announced over $1 million in federal funding awarded by @NIST for @MarylandMEP to support local manufacturing. Revitalizing American manufacturing is essential to creating jobs and growing our economy, all while keeping Maryland at the cutting edge.

It pains to me to say I just voted against a #Defense spending bill in committee for the first time. There are just too many poison pills that have nothing to do with our defense and, worse, drive a wedge in our committee’s previously bipartisan work for the sake of our security.

Our service members deserve the resources needed to execute their missions safely and support their families back home. Instead, Republicans are passing a #Defense funding bill that caters to their most extreme members. We're marking up the bill at 10 AM: piped.video/QdNwJlSs0aU

Spoke against efforts to undermine @TSA  pay parity as @AppropsDems mark-up the Homeland Security funding bill. These changes leave canine handlers, air marshals, investigators and explosive specialists – people that keep us safe – out in the cold. Watch: piped.video/dBYtIxvlfKc

I’m proud to be an original cosponsor of the Equality Act, which was just reintroduced today. This bill strengthens protections for LGBTQI+ individuals, women, people of color and religious minorities. It’s long past time we make the #EqualityAct the law of the land. 🏳️‍🌈

Joining my fellow @AppropsDems in pushing back on misguided and political cuts in the Homeland Security funding bill today. These cuts will open us to more (and more aggressive) cyber attacks, which threaten our security, economy and privacy. Watch: piped.video/watch?v=dBYtIxvl…
Enjoying time at the #CongressionalBaseballGame w/ my own #MD02 team and their families - pictured here w/ Gabby, my @USArmy fellow’s daughter! The game has been a #bipartisan tradition since 1962!
*Caveat: The one blue dot outlier was a joint request with a Republican member.
I’m a NO.

Per our napkin math, 70% of the funding for CPFs in this bill are for projects requested by Republicans. Less than a third for Dems. It’s a terrible bill for so many reasons, but this is just ridiculous. A lot of CPF requests from Democrats will benefit Republican voters.

Let’s talk about earmark equity. Look at this graph my staff put together on CPF funding in the AG bill, which @AppropsDems is marking up now. ZERO Democratic-led projects were funded above $1M, compared to 100+ Republican projects funded at $1M or more.
Happy birthday to my friend, @RepStenyHoyer! Maryland is so proud of all you have done for our state and our country. #TeamMaryland!
Just met w/ @GovWesMoore as a delegation for the first time in an official capacity. It’s our job to work together but also hold each other accountable.
Talking w/ @GovWesMoore and his all star cabinet, along w/ #TeamMaryland, about our shared priorities, values and goals. We work best when we work together.
On the 75th anniversary of the Women’s Armed Services Integration Act, I am celebrating the women who have served our country and fought to protect our freedoms. Happy #WomenVeteransDay!

Yesterday evening, #TeamDutch’s Danielle attended the Carroll Biz Challenge presented by the Carroll County Chamber of Commerce. The winner of the challenge wins $10K for their business - a great opportunity for local small businesses!

If MAGA extremists had forced a default on our nation's bills they would have plunged our economy into recession and wiped out over 7 million jobs.

I'm proud to be an original cosponsor of @CongBoyle's Debt Ceiling Reform Act.

Yesterday, I sat down with representatives from @NewtownAction and @AMarch4OurLives to discuss gun violence and safety in schools. Both groups were founded after devastating acts of gun violence in schools and I am grateful for their advocacy!

Former #TeamDutch member Amanda Rogers Thorpe was awarded a Congressional🎖️from @OSSSociety for her @HouseIntel work, including efforts to build a natl intelligence museum. Amanda was indispensable on defense issues for #MD02 and we are amazed by what she has accomplished since!
The #ChildTaxCredit lifted nearly 4 million children out of poverty in 2021 alone. It’s time to make the biggest middle class tax cut in a generation permanent by passing the #AmericanFamilyAct.

SNAP is an important resource for Marylanders struggling with food insecurity. Unrealistic work requirements ignore the unique circumstances of individuals and would leave many vulnerable families without food on the table.

On the anniversary of D-Day, we celebrate the servicemembers who courageously fought in this historic battle and honor those who did not return home. The sacrifices made 79 years ago paved the way to victory in WWII.

Founded by leaders who have experienced tragedies of gun violence in their schools, the @NASSP Principal Recovery Network seeks to help those who have suffered similar tragedies. Today, I met with them to discuss strategies to make schools and children safer.
The @POTUS continues to defy expectations on the economy, becoming the first president to oversee 13 million new jobs.

Happy Pride to the LGBTQI+ community in #MD02 and across the country. As state legislatures attack the rights of the LGBTQI+ community, we must continue to stand together and fight for LGBTQI+ people and ensure equality for all.

While we should have never been negotiating over something as sacred as our nation’s faith and credit, this deal avoids the most extreme of the proposed concessions. Most importantly, it protects the historic economic progress we have made over the last 2 years. Full statement:

Maryland's Congressional delegation is supporting @GovWesMoore's request for @CommerceGov to make a disaster declaration to help protect the #Chesapeake from the invasive blue catfish. Read our bipartisan statement from April: ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Memorial Day is a time to reflect on the sacrifices made by our military heroes and their families. My heart is with the #MD02 families and loved ones of those who made the ultimate sacrifice in service to our nation.
President Reagan put it best - defaulting will be catastrophic and put us on the path to complete economic instability.

Defaulting on our nation’s bills would kill 7 million jobs, wipe out $10 trillion in household wealth and plunge our economy into a recession.

In #Maryland alone, we could face a loss of nearly 120,000 jobs. We must not default.

Congressional Republicans are leading us on a path to default, devastating cuts and economic catastrophe. We must work together to come to an agreement before the house of cards collapses. Read my take, including #Maryland impacts, in @BaltimoreBanner: thebaltimorebanner.com/opini…

Thanks to @CBMMorg for stopping by today to discuss the importance of the Chesapeake Bay, the need to preserve regional history and maritime workforce development. The Chesapeake Bay is one of Maryland’s most valuable resources, and I am proud to support its preservation!

I am deeply saddened by the passing of George Pedersen, a longtime friend, respected leader and co-founder of @USNavy contractor @ManTech. He was one of the first CEOs that I met in Congress over 20 years ago when I was a freshman. My prayers are with George’s family.

Congratulations to @BaltCoPS student, Annette Mercado-Williams, for winning the #MD02 Congressional Art Competition! Her piece, entitled “Desensitization,” caught the eyes of my judges and is now on the way to the Capitol complex. Read more: ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

It’s National #TreatmentCourtMonth! These courts save lives and tax dollars, keep families together and reduce recidivism by offering treatment instead of incarceration. Proud to support these courts because, when one person rises from addiction, we all rise.

I voted for a resolution today expressing support for local law enforcement, but it should have included police at the federal level too. We must also put our words into action and fully fund police programs – not cut 22% as proposed by the House majority. Full statement:

#TeamDutch Military Fellow, Anna, successfully obtained a military record in 30 days for an #MD02 constituent that had been waiting for over a year. We are proud to serve our nation’s veterans. Way to go, Anna!

For 58 years, @HeadStartgov has provided critical support to families & children across the nation. Thank you for going the extra mile to prepare America’s children to succeed in school & life. #TBT w/ Head Start at Brooklyn Park Elementary School in 2015! #HappyBirthdayHeadStart

It was a pleasure meeting the new director of @NASAGoddard, Dr. Makenzie Lystrup, and the director of @NASA_Wallops, David Pearce, yesterday afternoon. We discussed support for our space missions as well as building out the space economy in #Maryland.

Yesterday, I met with @PCA_Daily, which was advocating for cement and concrete businesses like @LehighCement in #MD02. We discussed infrastructure funding, workforce development and reducing the industry’s carbon footprint. Great to learn more about the needs of local businesses.

I am proud of these three @NotreDamePrep1 students for being accepted to the @NavalAcademy. I had the honor of nominating Ms. Farley to the Academy earlier this year following an intensive interview process. Congratulations!
Moms are super heroes! Hope all the mothers and mother-figures had a special day. Special shout-out to my 101-year-old mother, Peggy, and my wife, Kay - both outstanding mothers!
If you are unable to attend, you can view the 50th Vietnam War Commemoration "Welcome Home Ceremony concert" live here: dvidshub.net/webcast/31825

This #NationalNursesWeek, I would like to thank all of the nurses in #MD02 and across the country for their tireless work to provide top-notch care to those in need. Be sure to thank your nurses this week, and every week!

Hat tip to the President and government of Peru for allowing this to happen. As a father and grandfather, I can't imagine the Holloway family's pain over the last 18 years. They deserve justice and closure.

The GOP immigration bill is draconian, inhumane and ineffective. We must work across the aisle to find a solution to our broken immigration system and to reflect the values of the majority of our nation, not the outspoken few. Full statement here:

Instead of offering support and protection to vulnerable children, the GOP border bill proposes to throw them into jail-like detention. It's a harsh, inhumane approach, reminiscent of failed Trump administration policies.

The @DeptofDefense is hosting a Welcome Home event near the National Mall to honor Vietnam Veterans and their families tomorrow through Saturday. I encourage my constituents to head down to DC and attend this commemorative event! Details: vietnamwar50th.com/welcomeho…

Big ✅ days are my favorite! Proudly presented @MedStarUMH one for $1.5 million today to help renovate the @CNHC_research, home to the world’s best hand surgeons, along w/ @ChrisVanHollen. This is a prime example of how community project funding directly supports #Marylanders.

Maryland is a beautiful state full of rich history and culture. That’s why #TeamMaryland secured $824k from @USDOT to preserve and make safety and accessibility improvements to multiple MD scenic byways. Read more: ruppersberger.house.gov/news…
Happy birthday to Myrna!

As we wrap up #SmallBusinessWeek, I want to celebrate all the small firms that are moving our country and economy forward. 2021 and 2022 were the strongest two years on record for new business applications. Small businesses are back under the Biden administration.

Congrats to @BaltCitySchools for winning $100K in the 1st phase of the new @ENERGY program to hire, train & support energy waste reduction managers in schools. The #bipartisan infrastructure law is helping to create jobs & healthier classrooms while reaching our pollution goals!

My bill to expand hospital-based violence intervention programs is back, this time w/ #bipartisan, bicameral support. Thanks to @SenatorCardin + @RogerMarshallMD for helping to end the cycle of violence in #Baltimore and around the country. More: ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

1 in 3 families in the US do not have enough diapers for their children. Our families deserve better. I am proud that @ActionMaryland has won $1.2 million from @OCS_ACFgov to distribute diapers alongside other antipoverty programs. Learn more here: acf.hhs.gov/ocs/programs/dia…

During Asian American, Native Hawaiian, and Pacific Islander Heritage Month, in #MD02 and across the country, we celebrate the vibrant history, culture and traditions of AANHPI communities. I wish everyone a Happy #AANHPIMonth!
Thank you, @SenatorCardin, for 56+ outstanding years in public service. I am proud to serve Maryland alongside you. Full statement here:

From his early days in Annapolis to the US Congress, @SenatorCardin has been behind so many wins for Maryland’s most vulnerable people and resources. His integrity is his legacy. Here’s a throwback from some of those early days, working to strengthen the @PortofBalt:

ruppersberger.house.gov/news…

Today, I’m joining my @AppropsDems colleagues and @FBI Director Wray to discuss the funding the FBI needs to make our nation and our communities safer. This is funding that saves lives in #MD02. Watch at 1:30PM: piped.video/qgnU3BuMpug

Defaulting would tank the economy, double unemployment, crash the stock market. Tying the debit limit to any condition – let alone conditions so extreme – is totally reckless. We must avoid default unconditionally, just as Congress did 3X during the previous Administration. More:
Always great to see a former #MD02 intern doing well! ⁦@fadelydc⁩ is now a VP w/ @cassidyinfo and was on the Hill to advocate for the #ChesapeakeBay! We’re proud of you, Will!

Enjoyed meeting w/ Evan Athanas of #MD02 biz @chesapeakebev repping @NBWA on the Hill today. We discussed workforce development, maintaining good-paying jobs in the district and other policies that support the responsible consumption and distribution of alcohol.

Proud to join my #TeamMaryland colleagues incl @ChrisVanHollen @SenatorCardin @RepKweisiMfume @MayorBMScott in formally announcing $2M from the #bipartisan infrastructure law to finally redevelop the Highway to Nowhere in west #Baltimore!

Vaccines don't administer themselves! To eliminate vaccine-preventable diseases globally, we need to invest in enough skilled, supported & protected #healthworkers in every community around the world to deliver vaccines and provide a long life for all. #WorldImmunizationWeek
Ditto what @ChrisVanHollen said. We are so proud of you, @RepRaskin!
Eid al-Fitr marks the end of the holy month of Ramadan. Wishing a joyous, blessed holiday to those who celebrate. Eid Mubarak!

It took a last minute show of bipartisanship and I am proud to have helped get it across the finish line. Still one of my favorite accomplishments in office. @SenBillNelson, thanks for the reminder of what we can achieve when we work together.  (4/4)

Bill responded with a story about the 2010 #NASA authorization, which set up many American commercial space companies for success. It helped advance the heavy lift rockets that will send us to the moon next year and Mars in the future. Also, it almost didn’t pass. (3/4)
Earlier, I had mentioned the importance of #bipartisanship. Everything good that has come out of Congress has been #bipartisan and that includes American space innovation. (2/4)

A short thread on #space.
